  "description": "This was an olive-backed bird with a tanager shape and bill. The olive on the back was dark in coloration. The wings were dark but not black and were WITHOUT WINGBARS and contrasted with the back. The wing feathers looked to be edged in green. The shoulder had an area of darker olive green. The tail was dark but not black. The bill, for a tanager was about the same size as the bill of a western. The bill color appeared light gray in my photos.Behaviors: Fed on the ground near a male Blue Grosbeak. Flushed easily and flew short distances before disappearing.Call: none heardPlumage: adult female likely",
